I tried to order on door dash but after I placed my order was told they don't have cod, only salmon and that also the menu price on door dash is wrong that it's actually $7 more. Clearly their own menu posted on their own website is $12.99 for cod, the salmon is $1 cheaper, so why would they try to charge me $8 more for a cheaper option? How is salmon even an acceptable alternative for cod? I really feel like they were trying to take advantage of me. Also on door dash you don't get the same options as in the restaurant, in the restaurant you get fries and a side, on door dash you only get fries or a side. So they charge you $8 more, don't provide any menu options, and you don't get the complete meal.  I can't even comprehend how they can be open when they can't deliver on fish and chips when they're called Bubby's Fish N' Chips. I was very excited for this and am now very disappointed.
